  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!), drizzle with&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;and season with both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and<strong>&nbsp;pepper </strong>and give it a good mix&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Place the tray in the oven and cook for 20-30 min or until the squash is tender and lightly browned&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the&nbsp;<strong>wheat berries&nbsp;</strong>to a pot with plenty of&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;and a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;(the same as you would for pasta)</p>\r\n<p>Bring back to the boil, then cook over a high heat for 12-15 min or until they're tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and leave to cool&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel the<strong>&nbsp;red onion[s]</strong>&nbsp;and cut into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Once the<strong> squash</strong> has been in the oven for 15 min, add the<strong>&nbsp;onion</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>dried&nbsp;sage</strong>&nbsp;to the tray, then&nbsp;return it to the oven for the remaining cooking time&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/829.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/829.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/829.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/829.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/829.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Juice the<strong>&nbsp;lemon[s]</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>lemon juice&nbsp;</strong>with&nbsp;2 tbsp&nbsp;[4 tbsp]&nbsp;<strong>olive oil </strong>and season with&nbsp;<strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;- this is your&nbsp;<strong>lemon dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash and dry the <strong>rocket salad&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Scatter the<strong> 3 seed mix all over the squash and onion 5 mins before they're done</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
